.SS macro FY_STACK_SAVE
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B FY_STACK_SAVE(void) 
Save the current stack pointer.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B Parameters
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBvoid\fP – no arguments
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Description
.sp
On compilers that provide \fB__builtin_stack_save()\fP (GCC, Clang) returns
the current stack pointer as a \fBvoid *\fP, allowing it to be restored later
with \fBFY_STACK_RESTORE()\fP\&. On other compilers returns \fB(void *)NULL\fP\&.
.sp
Use together with \fBFY_STACK_RESTORE()\fP to bound the stack growth of a loop
that calls \fBalloca()\fP on each iteration.
.SS Return
.sp
Opaque stack pointer value, or NULL if unsupported.
.SS macro FY_STACK_RESTORE
.INDENT 0.0
