.SS fy_ptr_align
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B void *fy_ptr_align(void *p, size_t align) 
Round a pointer up to the next multiple of \fBalign\fP\&.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B Parameters
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBp\fP (void*) – Pointer to align.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBalign\fP (size_t) – Alignment boundary in bytes (must be a power of two).
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Description
.sp
Does not allocate any memory; the caller is responsible for ensuring
the underlying buffer extends at least (@align \- 1) bytes past \fBp\fP\&.
.SS Return
.sp
\fBp\fP rounded up to the nearest multiple of \fBalign\fP\&.
