.TP
.B FYVL_SIZE_ENCODING_MAX() 
Maximum encoded length for a native size_t.
.UNINDENT
.SS Description
.sp
Equals \fBFYVL_SIZE_ENCODING_MAX_64\fP on 64\-bit platforms,
\fBFYVL_SIZE_ENCODING_MAX_32\fP on 32\-bit platforms.
.SH ATOMIC OPERATIONS
.sp
This header provides a thin, portable abstraction over C11 \fB<stdatomic.h>\fP
with graceful fallback for compilers that support \fB_Atomic\fP as an extension
(GCC without \fB\-std=c11\fP, Clang) and a last\-resort non\-atomic fallback for
toolchains that support neither.
.sp
\fBDetection macros\fP (defined by this header, not meant for direct use):
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
.INDENT 2.0
.TP
.B \fBFY_HAVE_STDATOMIC_H\fP   — \fB<stdatomic.h>\fP was successfully included;
the standard \fBatomic_*\fP functions and types
are available.
.UNINDENT
.IP \(bu 2
.INDENT 2.0
.TP
.B \fBFY_HAVE_C11_ATOMICS\fP   — the \fB_Atomic\fP qualifier is available, either
from \fB<stdatomic.h>\fP or as a compiler extension.
.UNINDENT
.IP \(bu 2
.INDENT 2.0
.TP
.B \fBFY_HAVE_ATOMICS\fP       — effective atomics are available (\fB_Atomic\fP
maps to a real atomic type).  When not defined,
\fB_Atomic(_x)\fP expands to plain \fB_x\fP and all
operations are non\-atomic single\-threaded stubs.
.UNINDENT
.IP \(bu 2
.INDENT 2.0
.TP
.B \fBFY_HAVE_SAFE_ATOMIC_OPS\fP — the underlying operations are properly
memory\-ordered (i.e. \fB<stdatomic.h>\fP is in
use).  Without this, operations are performed
as plain loads/stores with no memory barriers.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBPublic API\fP — all \fBfy_atomic_*\fP macros delegate to the selected backend:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBFY_ATOMIC()\fP                     — qualify a type as atomic
.IP \(bu 2
fy_atomic_flag                  — boolean flag type
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_load()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_store()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_exchange()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_compare_exchange_strong()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_compare_exchange_weak()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_fetch_add()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_fetch_sub()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_fetch_or()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_fetch_xor()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_fetch_and()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_flag_clear()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_flag_set()\fP / \fBfy_atomic_flag_test_and_set()\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_cpu_relax()\fP                  — emit a CPU relaxation hint (PAUSE/YIELD)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBfy_atomic_get_and_clear_counter()\fP — atomically read and subtract a counter
.UNINDENT
