.SS fy_cpu_relax
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B void fy_cpu_relax(void) 
Emit a CPU relaxation hint inside a spin\-wait loop.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B Parameters
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBvoid\fP – no arguments
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Description
.sp
Reduces power consumption and improves hyper\-threading performance on
x86/x86_64 (\fBPAUSE\fP), signals a yield on AArch64/ARM (\fBYIELD\fP),
and emits a low\-priority hint on PowerPC (\fBor 27,27,27\fP).
Falls back to a compiler memory barrier on unsupported architectures.
.sp
Use inside tight spin loops to avoid memory\-ordering penalties and
allow sibling hardware threads to make progress:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
while (!fy_atomic_load(&ready))
    fy_cpu_relax();
.EE
